      <div class="mdl-cell mdl-cell--3-offset-desktop mdl-cell--6-col-desktop mdl-cell--8-col-tablet">
        <h1>Mathieu Eveillard</h1>
        <div>Senior Fullstack JavaScript Developer, Trainer & Technical Coach</div>
        <div>10 years experience</div>
      </div>

      <div class="separator mdl-cell mdl-cell--3-offset-desktop mdl-cell--2-col-desktop"></div>

      <div class="mdl-cell mdl-cell--3-offset-desktop mdl-cell--6-col-desktop mdl-cell--8-col-tablet">
        <p>
          Hi! I build software, teach programming and write articles. I started programming when I was 10 by making
          games on a Texas Instrument TI-82 calculator, first in Basic, then in Assembly, C and C++. I hold an Engineer
          Degree of the <a href="https://www.polytechnique.edu/" target="_blank">Ecole Polytechnique</a>, 1st ranked
          French engineering school which offers a wide multidisciplinary scientific education, in particular in
          theoretical computer sciences.
        </p>

        <p>
          I'm based in Paris and currently work at <a href="http://www.arolla.fr/" target="_blank">Arolla</a> as a
          software developer and coach. My areas of focus are Single Page Applications, Functional and Reactive
          programming in TypeScript, software craftsmanship and agility. Though not an expert, I also have a strong
          sensitivity to UX.
        </p>

        <p>
          Prior to joining Arolla, I founded a social-oriented company providing access to energy to low-income people,
          then worked as a project director on a bunch of very large web applications (up to 5000 man-days).
        </p>

        <p>
          Art is another important dimension of my life. I'm mostly interested in
          <a href="http://www.mathieueveillard.com/" target="_blank">photography</a> and drawing as well as playing the
          piano and writing poetry. Also, previously, I ran a lot and I hit a few respectable personal bests: 36'04''
          (10km), 1h19' (half-marathon) and 3h02' (marathon).
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="mdl-cell mdl-cell--3-offset-desktop mdl-cell--6-col-desktop mdl-cell--8-col-tablet">
        <h2>Hire me</h2>
        I work at <a href="http://www.arolla.fr/" target="_blank">Arolla</a> and I can provide you with three types of
        services. Please contact me preferably by
        <a href="mailto:mathieu.eveillard@arolla.fr" target="_blank">email</a>.
        <ul class="long-ul">
          <li>
            <span class="emphasis">Software development</span>: if you're building a software product and need a senior
            developer with experience in Single Page Applications, Functional programming, Reactive programming, React
            and Redux, as well as a good proficiency on the back-end side, I'm likely to help you by committing a few
            weeks or months to solving your problems.
          </li>
          <li>
            <span class="emphasis">Technical training</span>: I've designed a 3 days intensive training to guide you
            through the learning of React and Redux. This training is best suited for back-end developers wishing to
            discover front-end development while keeping a strong focus on testability and clean code. This 3 days
            hand-on session is a unique opportunity to learn the challenging aspects of React and Redux, those you would
            probably need lots of time to discover by yourself. Find more details
            <a href="https://www.arolla.fr/training/front-end-craftsmanship/" target="_blank">here</a>.
          </li>
          <li>
            <span class="emphasis">Technical coaching</span>: writing code that works is easy, but writing long-lasting,
            maintainable code is an art. Of course, no one writes the best code on the first try, hence the philosophy
            of continuous improvement, core value of software craftsmanship and the clean code movement. Maintenability
            is usually achieved through an inforced concern on code legibility and a well suited testing strategy, which
            allows one to refactor safelly. Speaking of tests, Test Driven Development and Behaviour Driven Development
            bring a lot more than code coverage, since they are a way towards documenting your codebase and are
            associated to significant gains in working efficiency. As a technical coach, I'll be happy to help your
            teams of developers adopt these technics, whatever the paradigms or languages they use.
          </li>
          <!--
            <li>
              <span class="emphasis">Agile coaching</span>: shifting to agility often requires organizations to seek
              external help to explain, convince stakeholders and implement a concrete transformation. As an agile coach,
              I'll be happy to help you with the following facets of agility: user-centered design, transition from
              project to product management, continuous integration, continuous delivery, adoption of Scrum or Kanban
              frameworks, transition from manager to leader, and above all: promoting trust. You might be willing to refer
              to my article
              <a
              href="https://medium.com/@mathieueveillard/lagilit%C3%A9-ou-l-%C3%A9loge-de-la-confiance-9a4ae5e0604e"
              target="_blank"
              >L’agilité ou l’éloge de la confiance</a
              >
              (in French).
            </li>
          -->
        </ul>
      </div>

      <div class="mdl-cell mdl-cell--3-offset-desktop mdl-cell--6-col-desktop mdl-cell--8-col-tablet">
        <h2>Technical skills</h2>
        <ul>
          <li><span class="emphasis">Methodologies</span>: TDD, BDD, DDD, XP, Kanban, Scrum</li>
          <li>
            <span class="emphasis">Architectures</span>: Single Page Applications, REST, GraphQL, Hexagonal
            architecture, Event Sourcing, Microservices
          </li>
          <li>
            <span class="emphasis">Paradigms</span>: Functional programming, Reactive programming, good notions of
            Object Oriented Programming
          </li>
          <li><span class="emphasis">Languages</span>: JavaScript, TypeScript + RxJS/xstream</li>
          <li><span class="emphasis">Tests</span>: Jest, Enzyme, Chai, Stryker, TestCafé, Cucumber</li>
          <li><span class="emphasis">Front-end</span>: React, Redux, Next.js, MDL, OOCSS, BEM, SASS</li>
          <li><span class="emphasis">Back-end</span>: NodeJS, Express</li>
          <li><span class="emphasis">Databases</span>: PostgreSQL, MongoDB, ElasticSearch</li>
          <li><span class="emphasis">CI-CD</span>: CircleCI, Docker</li>
          <li><span class="emphasis">Cloud</span>: AWS S3, AWS Lambda, Serverless</li>
          <li><span class="emphasis">AI</span>: linear and logistic regression, neural networks, SVMs, K-means, PCA</li>
        </ul>
      </div>

