      <div class="mdl-cell mdl-cell--3-offset-desktop mdl-cell--6-col-desktop mdl-cell--8-col-tablet">
        <h2>Side projects</h2>
        <ul class="long-ul">
          <li>
            <div><span class="emphasis">Portfolio</span></div>
            <p>
              <a href="http://mathieueveillard.com/" target="_blank">mathieueveillard.com</a> |
              <a href="https://github.com/mathieueveillard/portfolio" target="_blank">monorepo</a>
            </p>
            <p>
              A turn-key solution for professional photographers wishing to showcase their work in a website suited to
              all devices. The admin interface allows an artist to choose one theme per series of photographs, as
              opposed to most solutions, where the same theme applies to all series.
            </p>
            <p>Portfolio is built of AWS-hosted microservices using React, Redux, Angular, Express and MongoDB.</p>
            <p><img src="<%= ROOT_URL %>/assets/PortfolioGallery.png" /></p>
            <p><img src="<%= ROOT_URL %>/assets/PortfolioAdmin.png" /></p>
          </li>
          <li>
            <div><span class="emphasis">Diary</span></div>
            <p><a href="https://github.com/mathieueveillard/diary" target="_blank">monorepo</a></p>
            <p>
              A diary app, elegant and powerful. Some of us write their thoughts and observations on paper, others
              prefer an online and mobile, yet secured, version. The application implements a Twitter-like infinite
              scrolling via <a href="https://www.npmjs.com/package/cycle-lazy-load" target="_blank">cycle-lazy-load</a>,
              which went open source.
            </p>
            <p>
              Diary is a PWA built of microservices using <a href="https://cycle.js.org/" target="_blank">Cycle.js</a>,
              Express, MongoDB and ElasticSearch, and is deployed with Docker.
            </p>
            <p><img src="<%= ROOT_URL %>/assets/Diary.png" /></p>
